Then you should make a custom renderer. The behavior you describe is the default with Sundown's own HTML renderer. I can't change much about it. By making a custom renderer you can override this method. For example:

~~~{python}
from misaka import Markdown, HtmlRenderer

class BleepRenderer(HtmlRenderer):
    def block_code(self, text, lang):
        if lang:
            lang = ' class="%s"' % lang
        else:
            lang  = ''
        return '\n<pre%s><code>%s</code></pre>\n' % (lang, text)

md = Markdown(BleepRenderer(), EXT_FENCED_CODE)

print(md.render("""
Some normal text

    var name = 'William Shakespeare';

Some normal text
"""))
~~~

