You can get the worker id by acessing the `slaveinput` [dictionary](https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-xdist/blob/master/xdist/remote.py#L16). Here's a fixture which makes that information available to tests or other fixtures:

```python
@pytest.fixture
def worker_id(request):
    if hasattr(request.config, 'slaveinput'):
        return request.config.slaveinput['slaveid']
    else:
        return 'master'
```

