@lelit, for `datetime.date` and `datetime.time` instances, I don't think we need to do anything. They are already formatted. (Also, I don't think anything can be done for `datetime.time` instances because there isn't enough info to create a unix timestamp from just time). 

I think those can be left with their default formatting.

The reason we need formatting options for `.timetuple()` instance is that it returns an object and not a formatted string.

